SIMPLE: pronounce
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pronounce
<hw>Pro*nounce"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Pronounced</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Pronounging</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>prononcer</ets>, L. <ets>pronunciare</ets>; <ets>pro</ets> before,
forth + <ets>nunciare</ets>, <ets>nuntiare</ets>, to announce. See
<er>Announce</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To utter articulately; to speak out or distinctly;
to utter, as words or syllables; to speak with the proper sound and
accent <as>as, adults rarely learn to <ex>pronounce</ex> a foreign
language correctly</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To utter officially or solemnly; to deliver, as a
decree or sentence; <as>as, to <ex>pronounce</ex> sentence of
death</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sternly he <qex>pronounced</qex>⟦br⟧
The rigid interdiction.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To speak or utter rhetorically; to deliver; to
recite; <as>as, to <ex>pronounce</ex> an oration</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Speak the speech, I pray you, as I <qex>pronounced</qex> it to
you.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To declare or affirm; <as>as, he <ex>pronounced</ex>
the book to be a libel; he <ex>pronounced</ex> the act to be a
fraud.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The God who hallowed thee and blessed,⟦br⟧
<qex>Pronouncing</qex> thee all good.</q> <rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To deliver; utter; speak. See
<er>Deliver</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pronounce</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pronounce
<hw>Pro*nounce"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To give a pronunciation; to articulate; <as>as, to
<ex>pronounce</ex> faultlessly</as>.</def> <rj><au>Earle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make declaration; to utter on opinion; to speak
with confidence.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Dr. H.
More.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pronounce</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Pronounce
<hw>Pro*nounce"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Pronouncement; declaration;
pronunciation.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pronounceable</ent>⟦br⟧
